 install hlint\n\n# Pre-built binaries available from GitHub releases:\n# https://github.com/ndmitchell/hlint/releases\n```\n\n### Command Line Usage\n\n```bash\n# Lint a single file\nhlint Main.hs\n\n# Lint an entire project (recursively)\nhlint .\n\n# Lint specific directories\nhlint src/ app/\n\n# Apply suggestions automatically (rewrites files in place)\nhlint --refactor --refactor-options=\"--inplace\" Main.hs\n\n# Generate a report\nhlint . --report\n\n# Output as JSON (useful for CI tooling)\nhlint . --json\n\n# Show only errors (ignore warnings and suggestions)\nhlint . --only=Error\n\n# Ignore specific hints\nhlint . --ignore=\"Use camelCase\" --ignore=\"Redundant bracket\"\n\n# Use a specific configuration file\nhlint . --hint=.hlint.yaml\n\n# Set the exit code behavior for CI (default: non-zero on hints found)\nhlint .   # exits non-zero if any hints found -- good for CI as-is\n```\n\n### CI Integration (GitHub Actions Example)\n\n```yaml\n- name: Run HLint\n  uses: haskell-actions/hlint-run@v2\n  with:\n    path: '[\"src/\", \"app/\"]'\n    fail-on: warning\n```\n\nOr simply in a script step:\n\n```yaml\n- name: Lint\n  run: hlint .\n```\n\n### Pre-Commit Hook\n\nIn a `.pre-commit-config.yaml`:\n\n```yaml\nrepos:\n  - repo: https://github.com/haskell/actions\n    hooks:\n      - id: hlint\n```\n\nOr a simple git hook script (`.git/hooks/pre-commit`):\n\n```bash\n#!/bin/sh\nhlint $(git diff --cached --name-only --diff-filter=ACM | grep '\\.hs$')\n```\n\n### Configuration File (.hlint.yaml)\n\nPlace a `.hlint.yaml` in your project root to customize behavior:\n\n```yaml\n# Ignore specific rules\n- ignore: {name: \"Use camelCase\"}\n- ignore: {name: \"Redundant bracket\", within: Main}\n\n# Set severity\n- warn: {name: \"Use head\"}\n\n# Custom hints\n- hint: {lhs: \"map f (map g x)\", rhs: \"map (f . g) x\", name: \"Fuse maps\"}\n```\n\n### For Your Project (git-all)\n\nGiven that `git-all` is a single-module project (`Main.hs`), the simplest invocation would be:\n\n```bash\nhlint Main.hs\n```\n\nOr if integrating into a Nix flake, you could add `hlint` to your `devShell` packages in `flake.nix` and run it as part of your development workflow.\n\n---\n\n## Other Tools (and Why HLint Is Still Primary)\n\n| Tool | Purpose | Status (2025) | CI Suitability |\n|------|---------|---------------|----------------|\n| **HLint** | Style/idiom linting | Actively maintained, widely used | Excellent -- the standard choice |\n| **Stan** | Static analysis (anti-patterns, partial functions) | Maintenance has been inconsistent; GHC version lag is common | Decent if it supports your GHC version |\n| **Weeder** | Dead code detection | Maintained, but requires HIE files from a full build | Good as a secondary CI check |\n| **GHC -Wall -Werror** | Compiler warnings as errors | Always available | Essential baseline, complements HLint |\n\n**Stan** is interesting for catching things HLint does not (e.g., partial function usage, infinite type class constraints), but it has historically lagged behind GHC releases and can be difficult to build with the latest compiler. It is not nearly as universally adopted as HLint.\n\n**Weeder** finds dead/unused code, which is valuable but requires a full project build with HIE files enabled (`-fwrite-ide-info`). It serves a different purpose than linting and is best used as a supplementary CI step.\n\n**GHC -Wall -Werror** should always be your baseline. This catches genuine issues at the type/compiler level. HLint complements this by catching stylistic and idiomatic issues that the compiler does not flag.\n\n---\n\n## Recommended CI Setup (Summary)\n\nFor a robust Haskell CI lint pipeline:\n\n1. **Primary linter**: `hlint .` -- fast, no build required, catches style/idiom issues\n2. **Compiler warnings**: Build with `-Wall -Werror` in your `.cabal` file or GHC options\n3. **Optional secondary**: `weeder` for dead code detection (if you have HIE files in your build)\n\nHLint is the clear, unambiguous answer for \"the most commonly used and recommended Haskell linter.\"</result>\n<usage><total_tokens>4359</total_tokens><tool_uses>3</tool_uses><duration_ms>42897</duration_ms></usage>\n</task-notification>\nFull transcript available at: /private/tmp/claude-501/-Users-johnw-src-git-all/eee069e4-0fd1-4321-8699-82b793c6e582/tasks/a4e84b26cb80705c3.output",
